							  <h4 class="entry-overline">Baseball</h4>
<h1 class="entry-title">Texas shortstop Joe Baker was arrested for public intoxication</h1>
<p class="publish-time">Posted May 23rd, 2016</p>							<div class="entry-author-meta clearfix">
      <div class="author-img pull-left">
      <img src="https://d4o3oxzf7m9sj.cloudfront.net/uMwLs-JOWWb_vbn8BEdQSxUGDuo=/fit-in/120x120/www.hookem.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Ryan-Autullo-square.jpg" class="img-responsive avatar" />
    </div>
    <p class="byline">
      <span class="author-name">
      <a href="https://www.hookem.com/author/rautullo">        Ryan Autullo
      </a>    </span>
                  <span class="author-underline">American-Statesman Staff</span>
  </p>
  <p class="contact-info">
          <i class="fa fa-twitter"></i>
                        <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/user?screen_name=autulloaas" target="_blank" class="social-action" data-network="twitter" data-action="follow-staff" data-social-target="autulloaas">@autulloaas</a>
                    </p>
</div>						</header>

												<div class="ad text-center story-ad">
	<div class="ad-label">Advertisement</div>
		<div class="ad-content">
		<div id="as07-wrapper">
			<div id="as07" class="center-block"></div>
		</div>
		</div>
</div>

												<p>Texas shortstop Joe Baker was arrested for public intoxication on May 12 after he admitted to UTPD to consuming three or four drinks earlier in the evening.</p>
<p>According to the arrest affidavit, an officer found Baker sitting on the ground at the corner of San Jacinto and Martin Luther King Jr. boulevards next to a dried puddle of vomit. The officer said he detected a strong odor of alcohol coming from Baker.</p>
<figure id="attachment_12329"  class="wp-caption alignleft"><img srcset="https://d4o3oxzf7m9sj.cloudfront.net/cSUVL42vO-naYmOQwJrAunYCyoQ=/fit-in/360x0/www.hookem.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Baker-Joseph-Michael-20-years-of-age-UTPD.jpg 360w, https://d4o3oxzf7m9sj.cloudfront.net/2JgLJLcS_RemhfrQabGoAZcvLH8=/480x600/www.hookem.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Baker-Joseph-Michael-20-years-of-age-UTPD.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 768px) 350px, 98vw" class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-12329" alt="Travis County booking mugshot of Texas shortstop Joe Baker."><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Travis County booking mugshot of Texas shortstop Joe Baker.</figcaption></figure>
<p>Asked by the officer for the identity of Mickey Mouse, Baker responded &#8220;a cat.&#8221;</p><div class="ad text-center visible-xs-block">
  <div class="ad-label">Advertisement</div>
  <div class="ad-content">
      <div id="as06" class="center-block"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>According to a team spokeswoman, Longhorns coach Augie Garrido took action by suspending Baker for the team&#8217;s home game against Texas State on May 17. Baker was back in the starting lineup for the first two games of last weekend&#8217;s series against Baylor.</p>
<p>Baker, a sophomore from McKinney, has started 30 games and is hitting .250 with 16 RBIs. Arguably the team&#8217;s top hitter a month ago, Baker is mired in an 0-for-16 slump and has seen his average dip by 63 points over his past 10 games.</p>
<p>On Wednesday, Texas opens play in the Big 12 tournament against Oklahoma State. First pitch is scheduled for 7:30 p.m.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>


